orbitdeck (0.36.8-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Reachability sweep across all screens: the Orbital Analysis Info readout and
    the Radio link-budget readout could be taller than the window and were clipped
    at the bottom (Element-set / Uplink sections) with no scrollbar on shorter
    displays. Both readouts now live in a vertical scroller. Audited every screen
    in its default state, every tab on every tabbed screen, and the OSCARLOCATOR
    Sim's drive modes; no other clipped-without-scroll content remains.

 -- Paul Stoetzer, N8HM <noreply@example.com>  Mon, 23 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000

orbitdeck (0.36.7-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Fix the lab "Challenges..." launcher (and the Trace-orbits control) appearing
    to be missing. They live at the bottom of the OSCARLOCATOR Sim control column,
    which can be taller than the window; on shorter displays the bottom of the
    column was clipped with no scrollbar, so those lab-mode controls fell off the
    bottom. The control column is now wrapped in a vertical scroller, so they are
    reachable. The challenges feature itself was never removed.

 -- Paul Stoetzer, N8HM <noreply@example.com>  Mon, 23 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000

orbitdeck (0.36.6-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Revert the v0.36.4 bundle-size reductions, which broke the GitHub builds:
    removed the _trim_datas data filter and the scipy/pandas excludes from the
    PyInstaller spec (now byte-identical to the pre-0.36.4 spec). BUILD.md keeps
    the explanation of why the Windows build is larger, with a caution against
    aggressive trimming without testing every platform's artifact.
  * Fix printed reports drawing content on top of the centred branding credit at
    the foot of each page. The full satellite report's pass-progression timeline
    chart printed its x-axis label over the branding; raised that chart and the
    content-flow / table / polar-grid / mutual-row floors so all content clears
    the footer. OSCARLOCATOR sheets were already fine and are unchanged. Handouts
    were verified clear (a margin note was added to keep them that way).

 -- Paul Stoetzer, N8HM <noreply@example.com>  Mon, 23 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000

orbitdeck (0.36.5-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Fix tabs that stayed unclickable on macOS (reported on the Learn screen's
    Pointing and Link budget tabs). Three robustness changes to the tab bar:
    tabs now respond to <ButtonRelease-1> as well as <Button-1> (macOS/Aqua does
    not always deliver <Button-1> to a nested label); the tab font is now the
    native TkDefaultFont instead of the Linux-only "DejaVu Sans" that macOS
    silently substitutes with different metrics; and the grouped/wrapping tab
    layout is recomputed once geometry settles and grows the strip to fit wrapped
    rows, so no tab is ever clipped out of the clickable area. Reflow and the
    deferred relayout preserve the current tab instead of snapping to the first.

 -- Paul Stoetzer, N8HM <noreply@example.com>  Mon, 23 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000

orbitdeck (0.36.4-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Reduce bundle size, especially on Windows (whose conda-forge dependency stack
    is heavier than the pip wheels used on Linux/macOS): exclude scipy and pandas
    (unused by OrbitDeck; only optional for cartopy), and trim large unused data
    files via the spec's _trim_datas -- chiefly the PROJ datum-shift grids (only
    proj.db is kept), matplotlib sample data, and cartopy/matplotlib test data.
    Documented the cause of the Windows/other size gap in BUILD.md.

 -- Paul Stoetzer, N8HM <noreply@example.com>  Mon, 23 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000

orbitdeck (0.36.3-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Fix tabs that could feel unclickable (reported on the Learn screen's
    "Pointing" and "Link budget" tabs). The click was bound only to the tab's
    text label, so clicks landing on the surrounding padding or the 2px underline
    strip did nothing. The whole tab area (holder, label, and indicator) is now
    clickable. This affects every tabbed screen, not just Learn.

 -- Paul Stoetzer, N8HM <noreply@example.com>  Mon, 23 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000

orbitdeck (0.36.2-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * DX Doppler: display the four dial frequencies to the Hz (was kHz-rounded), so
    the home station's small Doppler near closest approach is visible instead of
    appearing frozen. The underlying engine was already correct and full-precision
    (CSV export was unaffected); this is a display-resolution fix. Added
    regression tests covering home-station Doppler resolution, inverting-
    transponder passband mapping, and DX-station dial locking in the fixed modes.

 -- Paul Stoetzer, N8HM <noreply@example.com>  Mon, 23 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000

orbitdeck (0.36.1-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Readability/consistency: informational text no longer sits on a stray
    panel-coloured rectangle -- the shared label and control-container styles use
    the window background, so only buttons, entry fields, sliders and the
    deliberate readout cards have their own background.
  * Fix the Settings screen being cut off at the bottom on short displays (e.g. a
    MacBook Air at default resolution): the form is now wrapped in a vertical
    scroller (new make_vscroll_frame helper) with an auto-hiding scrollbar and
    mouse-wheel support.

 -- Paul Stoetzer, N8HM <noreply@example.com>  Mon, 23 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000

orbitdeck (0.36.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Add DX Doppler to the Mutual Windows detail view: double-clicking a window now
